    {
      "id": 874835,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "Monero's restricted RPC mode is designed to limit the information exposed to untrusted clients. The `get_info` endpoint correctly hides alternative block metadata by returning `alt_blocks_count` as `0`.\n\nHowever, the separate `get_alt_blocks_hashes` endpoint was not restricted in the same way and continued to return the list of alternative block hashes.\n\nThis inconsistency allowed clients connected to the restricted RPC port to learn whether alternative blocks existed and retrieve their exact hashes.",
      "updated_at": "2026-07-13T15:58:57.607Z",
      "can_view?": true,
      "can_create?": false,
